{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GeJimhuQgTGsiYns1Mb4UZ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information you requested. Let me compile the complete report.\n\n## Report: Current State of Profile Routes and Related Infrastructure\n\n### 1. **Profile Routes File** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/routes/profile.ts`)\n\n**Full Content (lines 1-143):**\n\nThe file defines two endpoints:\n\n- **GET `/transactions`** (lines 34-89): Fetches paginated transaction history for authenticated wallet\n  - Query parameters: `cursor` (string), `limit` (number, clamped to max 50), `game` (optional game filter)\n  - Accepts both DB game names and frontend names via `TO_DB_GAME` mapping\n  - Returns transactions with frontend game names, pagination cursor\n  - Calls `db.getTransactions(wallet, cursor, limit, dbGame)`\n\n- **POST `/confirm-tx`** (lines 92-139): Records confirmed on-chain transactions\n  - Body requires: `game`, `matchId`, `txType`, `txSig`, `amountLamports`\n  - Validates `txType` is one of: `[\"deposit\", \"refund\"]`\n  - Maps game name to DB name before storing\n  - Calls `db.insertTransaction({wallet, game, matchId, txType, amountLamports, txSig})`\n\n**Game Name Mappings:**\n- `GAME_TO_FRONTEND` (lines 15-19): Maps DB names to frontend IDs (coinflip→coinflip, lord→lord-of-rngs, closecall→close-call)\n- `TO_DB_GAME` (lines 22-28): Maps both DB and frontend names to canonical DB names (accepts both \"lord\" and \"lord-of-rngs\" → \"lord\")\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Type Definitions and Method Signatures from `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/db.ts`**\n\n**PlayerProfile Type** (lines 186-196):\n```typescript\nexport interface PlayerProfile {\n  id: number;\n  user_id: string;\n  wallet: string;\n  username: string;\n  username_updated_at: Date | null;\n  avatar_url: string | null;\n  heat_multiplier: number;\n  points_balance: number;\n  created_at: Date;\n}\n```\n\n**Supporting Stats Types** (lines 198-223):\n\n- **PlayerStats** (lines 198-204): `{ gamesPlayed: number; totalWagered: bigint; totalWins: number; winRate: number; netPnl: bigint; }`\n- **PublicPlayerStats** (lines 206-210): `{ gamesPlayed: number; totalWins: number; winRate: number; }`\n- **WinStreaks** (lines 212-215): `{ current: number; best: number; }`\n- **GameBreakdownStats** (lines 217-223): `{ gamesPlayed: number; totalWagered: bigint; totalWins: number; winRate: number; netPnl: bigint; }`\n\n**Method Signatures in Db Interface** (lines 482, 487, 494, 501):\n\n1. **`getPlayerStats(wallet: string): Promise<PlayerStats>`** (line 482)\n   - Implementation (lines 1162-1193): Computes from transactions table\n   - Counts distinct matches with 'deposit' as games_played\n   - Sums 'deposit' amounts for total_wagered\n   - Counts distinct matches with 'payout' as total_wins\n   - Calculates net_pnl: sum(payout + refund amounts) - sum(deposit amounts)\n   - Returns winRate as totalWins / gamesPlayed (or 0)\n\n2. **`getPublicPlayerStats(wallet: string): Promise<PublicPlayerStats>`** (line 487)\n   - Implementation (lines 1196-1202): Calls `getPlayerStats()` internally\n   - Returns only public fields: gamesPlayed, totalWins, winRate (no totalWagered, netPnl)\n\n3. **`getGameBreakdown(wallet: string): Promise<Record<string, GameBreakdownStats>>`** (line 494)\n   - Implementation (lines 1205-1251): Groups transactions by game\n   - Maps DB names (coinflip, lord, closecall) to frontend names (coinflip, lord-of-rngs, close-call)\n   - Omits games with zero activity\n   - Same stats calculation as getPlayerStats, per-game\n\n4. **`getWinStreaks(wallet: string): Promise<WinStreaks>`** (line 501)\n   - Implementation (lines 1254-1296): Calculates consecutive win streaks\n   - Matches grouped by match_id, ordered by most recent first\n   - Win = has 'payout' transaction, Loss = has 'deposit' but no 'payout'\n   - Refund-only matches excluded from streak calculation\n   - Returns { current: consecutive wins from most recent, best: longest streak ever }\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Route Registration from `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/index.ts`**\n\n**Profile Route Registration** (lines 94-99):\n\n```typescript\n// Profile routes — authenticated GET endpoints (require JWT on all methods)\napp.use(\n  \"/profile/*\",\n  createJwtAuthMiddleware({ jwtSecret: config.jwtSecret, requireAllMethods: true }),\n);\napp.route(\"/profile\", createProfileRoutes({ db }));\n```\n\n**Pattern:**\n1. JWT middleware is applied to all `/profile/*` paths (line 95-98)\n   - `requireAllMethods: true` means all HTTP methods (GET, POST, etc.) require authentication\n   - Middleware extracts wallet from JWT and stores in `c.get(\"wallet\")`\n2. Routes are registered at line 99 via `app.route(\"/profile\", createProfileRoutes({ db }))`\n3. Profile routes receive only `{ db }` as dependency\n\n**Context for Related Routes:**\n- Routes use `c.get(\"wallet\")` to access authenticated wallet (set by JWT middleware)\n- Similar pattern used for `/referral/*` (lines 101-106) which also requires JWT on all methods\n- Fairness routes use JWT middleware but with `requireAllMethods` defaulting to false (line 111), allowing GET public access\n\n---\n\n**Summary of Key Points:**\n- Profile routes currently support only **transaction history** (GET) and **transaction confirmation** (POST)\n- Stats methods exist in DB layer but are **not exposed via profile routes**\n- Stats methods return appropriate types: full stats (with PnL) vs public stats (sanitized), per-game breakdown, and win streaks\n- Authentication is enforced at middleware level via JWT bearer token\n- Game name mapping is bidirectional to support both DB and frontend naming conventions"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b10d11a6-64a8-4246-9053-4c7d6bdc5315","uuid":"a1555832-57fa-4f68-977f-421f66007353","timestamp":"2026-03-31T15:12:42.740Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"